# Naming Conventions

## Directory Structure

Organize `src/` by service / feature domain. Group related connector, batch, and mapper files together:

```
src/
  index.ts                          # Entry point — register all elements here
  MyService/
    MyServiceApplication.ts         # Application (auth provider)
    Connector/
      MyServiceGetResource.ts
      MyServiceCreateResource.ts
    Batch/
      MyServiceListResources.ts
    CustomNode/
      MyServiceToOtherMapper.ts
    __tests__/
      MyServiceGetResource.ts
      MyServiceCreateResource.ts
      Data/
        MyServiceGetResource/
          input.json
          output.json
          mock.json
  OtherService/
    OtherServiceApplication.ts
    Connector/
      ...
  Mapper/
    ServiceAToServiceB/             # Cross-service mappers can live in a shared Mapper/ dir
      ServiceAToServiceBMapper.ts
```

## Element Names (getName())

- **Kebab-case**, prefixed by service name.
- Must be **unique** across the entire worker.
- Once deployed in a topology, **never rename** — the Orchesty platform references nodes by name.

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| Connector | `{service}-{action}` | `my-service-get-resource` |
| Batch | `{service}-{action}` | `my-service-list-resources` |
| CustomNode | `{descriptive-name}` | `map-service-a-to-service-b` |
| Application | `{service}` | `my-service` |

## File & Class Names

- **PascalCase** for class names and file names.
- File name must match the class name: `MyServiceGetResource.ts` -> `class MyServiceGetResource`.
- One class per file.

| Type | Class Suffix | Example |
|------|-------------|---------|
| Connector | none or `Connector` | `MyServiceGetResource` |
| Batch | `Batch` | `MyServiceListResourcesBatch` |
| CustomNode / Mapper | `Mapper` or `Filter` | `ServiceAToServiceBMapper` |
| Application | `Application` | `MyServiceApplication` |

## Exports

- Use `export default class` for all elements (connectors, batches, custom nodes, applications).
- Export `IInput`, `IOutput` interfaces and a `NAME` constant alongside the default class.
- Keep one default export per file.

```typescript
export const NAME = 'my-service-get-resource';

export interface IInput { ... }
export interface IOutput { ... }

export default class MyServiceGetResource extends AConnector { ... }
```

## Test Files

- Test files go in `__tests__/` next to the source.
- Test file name matches the source file name (without `.test`): `__tests__/MyServiceGetResource.ts`.
- Data fixtures live in `__tests__/Data/{ClassName}/`.
